      "width": 250,
      "height": 219,
      "content": "Create a complete mobile app wireframe for Dokimos, an identity verification vault. Design 5 screens as separate frames side by side on the canvas, each 390px wide by 844px tall (iPhone 14 size). Use Pencil's built-in component library, auto-layout, and design system tokens throughout.\nDESIGN SYSTEM — apply consistently across all screens:\nPrimary color: Deep navy #0F1B4C\nAccent color: Indigo #4F46E5\nSuccess color: Emerald #059669\nBackground: Pure white #FFFFFF\nSurface: Light gray #F8F9FA\nText primary: #111827\nText secondary: #6B7280\nBorder: #E5E7EB\nFont: Use Pencil's default sans-serif, clean and minimal\nBorder radius: 12px for cards, 8px for buttons, 999px for pills\nSpacing unit: 8px base grid\nShadow: Subtle, single layer, 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.08)\nSCREEN 1 — \"Why Dokimos\" (Landing) Frame label: \"01 — Landing\" Layout from top to bottom:\nStatus bar at top (auto, standard mobile)\nTop navigation: Dokimos wordmark in navy on the left, \"Sign in\" text link on the right\nHero section (centered, generous padding 32px sides): Large headline in 32px bold navy: \"Your identity, verified once.\" Second line same size: \"Used everywhere.\" Below that, 16px gray subtitle: \"Stop uploading your passport to every new app. Verify once — share only what each service actually needs. Nothing more.\"\nIllustration area: A simple abstract graphic — three company logos (generic bank, generic exchange, generic app) on the right connected by lines flowing into a single shield icon on the left labeled \"Dokimos vault.\" Shows the concept visually without being literal.\nTrust strip: Three horizontally arranged small cards with icons. Card 1: shield icon + \"Hardware-level privacy\" + \"Processed in sealed hardware\". Card 2: lock icon + \"You control sharing\" + \"Share only what's asked\". Card 3: checkmark icon + \"Verify once\" + \"Works everywhere after\"\nPrimary CTA button: Full width, indigo fill, white text, 52px height, rounded 12px: \"Verify Your Identity — It's Free\"\nBelow button: Small centered gray text \"Takes 2 minutes. No wallet required.\"\nBottom: Thin separator then small text \"Already verified? Sign in\"\nSCREEN 2 — \"Verify Once\" (Upload Flow) Frame label: \"02 — Upload\" This is the one-time setup screen. It should feel significant — like the user is doing something that will save them time forever. Layout from top to bottom:\nTop navigation: Back arrow on left, \"Step 1 of 2\" progress indicator centered, nothing on right\nProgress bar: Full width, 4px height, indigo fill at 50%, gray remainder\nSection header: 24px bold \"Upload your ID\" with subtitle \"This is the only time you'll need to do this.\"\nDocument type selector: Two large cards side by side with 12px gap. Each card 160px wide, 80px tall, rounded 12px, 1px border. Left card: ID card icon + \"Driver's License\" — selected state has indigo border and light indigo fill. Right card: passport icon + \"Passport\" — unselected state gray border.\nUpload zone: Large dashed border rectangle, 48px corner radius, full width, 200px tall. Center content: upload arrow icon in indigo circle (48px), below it \"Drop your ID here\" in 16px medium, below that \"or tap to browse\" in 14px gray. Subtle dashed border in gray.\nSecurity reassurance card: Light gray background card, full width, 16px padding. Left side: small lock icon in indigo. Right side: \"Your document never leaves sealed hardware\" in 14px medium, below \"Processed inside Intel TDX TEE — not even Dokimos can see it\" in 12px gray.\nScanning animation placeholder: Show a static representation of the scanning state — the ID outline with a horizontal glowing indigo line across the middle, label below: \"Processing inside TEE...\" in 14px indigo with a small spinner. This is the state shown while verification runs.\nPrimary CTA button: Full width indigo \"Verify Document\" — disabled/gray state until file is selected.\nSCREEN 3 — \"You Own This\" (Vault Dashboard) Frame label: \"03 — Vault\" This is the most important screen for the user — it should feel like they own something valuable, not like a data table. Layout from top to bottom:\nTop navigation: Dokimos wordmark left, avatar/initials circle right (JO for Jordan)\nVerified banner: Full width card, emerald green left border accent (4px), light green background. Left: green checkmark circle icon. Center: \"Identity Verified\" in 16px bold green, below \"4/1/2026 at 5:33 PM\" in 12px gray. Right: small pill badge \"Processed in TEE\" with lock icon — tapping shows tooltip \"Your document was processed in sealed Intel TDX hardware\"\nSection header: \"Your Verified Attributes\" in 18px bold, right side: \"4 attributes\" in 14px gray\nAttribute cards: Stacked list, each card full width, 72px tall, white background, 1px border, 12px radius, 16px padding. Each card has: left icon in colored circle (40px), center column with attribute name in 14px gray and value in 16px bold navy, right side \"Share\" button in small indigo outline pill. Cards: (1) person icon blue circle — \"Full Name\" / \"Jordan Lee\" / Share. (2) shield icon green circle — \"Age Over 21\" / green checkmark + \"Verified\" / Share. (3) calendar icon purple circle — \"Document Expiry\" / green checkmark + \"Valid\" / Share. (4) globe icon orange circle — \"Nationality\" / \"United States\" / Share.\nActivity section header: \"Recent Activity\" in 18px bold\nActivity feed: Two items. Each item: small circle icon left, description center, timestamp right. Item 1: green dot — \"Identity verified\" — \"Today, 5:33 PM\". Item 2: gray dot — \"Vault created\" — \"Today, 5:33 PM\"\nBottom tab bar: 3 tabs — Vault (active, indigo), Activity, Settings\nSCREEN 4 — \"One Tap Approval\" (Share Flow) Frame label: \"04 — Share\" This is the moment Jordan realizes the product's value — one tap instead of re-uploading. Should feel like a permission dialog, clean and trustworthy. Layout: This is a bottom sheet modal overlaid on a blurred version of Screen 3.\nBackground: Blurred/dimmed version of the vault dashboard (show as gray overlay)\nBottom sheet: White card, top 24px radius, slides up from bottom, takes up 60% of screen height\nSheet handle: Small gray pill at top center (standard iOS/Android bottom sheet)\nTop of sheet: Company identity section — generic bank logo placeholder circle, \"Acme Brokerage\" in 18px bold, \"is requesting verification\" in 14px gray\nDivider line\nRequested attributes section header: \"They're asking for:\" in 14px gray uppercase small\nRequested attribute list: Each item has checkmark icon left, attribute name center, nothing right. Items: \"Full Name\", \"Age Over 21\", \"Document Not Expired\". Each 44px tall with thin bottom border.\nPrivacy note: Light gray card with eye-slash icon: \"They will NOT receive your actual ID — only cryptographic confirmation of these attributes\"\nTwo buttons stacked: Primary full-width indigo \"Approve & Share\" 52px. Secondary full-width white with gray border \"Deny Request\" 52px.\nBottom: tiny gray text \"Powered by Dokimos · Cryptographically verified\"\nSCREEN 5 — \"The Proof\" (Relying Party View) Frame label: \"05 — Verified Receipt\" This is what Acme Brokerage sees. Should feel like an official verified certificate — authoritative and trustworthy. Layout from top to bottom:\nTop: Dokimos wordmark centered, small gray \"Verification Receipt\" subtitle\nHero result: Large centered section. Giant green checkmark circle (80px, emerald fill, white check). Below: \"Verified\" in 32px bold emerald. Below: \"Age Over 21\" in 20px navy. Below: \"Verified on April 1, 2026 at 5:33 PM\" in 14px gray.\nAttestation card: White card, 1px border, 12px radius, 16px padding. Header \"Verification Details\" in 14px bold. Rows: \"Attribute\" / \"Age Over 21\". \"Result\" / green \"True ✓\". \"Verified at\" / timestamp. \"Expires\" / \"Never (cryptographic proof)\".\nTrust section: \"How is this verified?\" — accordion closed state showing just the question with a chevron. When opened (show open state): paragraph explaining TEE in plain English. \"This verification was generated by code running inside an Intel TDX Trusted Execution Environment. The signature below was produced by a wallet that only that specific, auditable code can access.\"\nTechnical verification buttons: Two full-width outline buttons stacked. Button 1: external link icon + \"Verify Signature on Etherscan\". Button 2: external link icon + \"View Code on EigenCloud Dashboard\".\nRaw data section: Dark navy/black terminal-style card. Monospace font 11px. Shows: message, messageHash, signature (truncated), signer address. Small \"Copy\" button top right.\nBottom: Small gray text \"Issued by Dokimos · Cryptographic identity infrastructure\"\nGLOBAL DESIGN NOTES: Use Pencil's auto-layout feature on every card and list item so spacing is consistent. Apply the design system colors as Pencil variables so they're reusable. Use Pencil's built-in icon library for all icons — do not use emoji. Every interactive element (buttons, cards, share pills) should show a hover/pressed state using Pencil's component variants. Maintain 24px horizontal padding on all screens consistently. All text should follow an 8px baseline grid. The overall feeling should be: Linear meets Stripe meets a premium consumer app. Clean, trustworthy, not crypto, not corporate, not startup-generic."
    },
